[
  {
    "op": "MODIFY",
    "section": "action_execution",
    "target_id": "acti-014",
    "content": "IF a user requests to split payment across multiple payment methods for a single order at the time of purchase → THEN refuse the request and inform the user that a single payment method must be used for that order; offer alternatives such as removing items to reduce the total, using a different single payment method, or placing a new separate order to use a different card. EXCEPTION: for order exchanges or modifications that create a price difference (additional charge or refund), it is permitted to apply the price difference to a different payment method than the original order (resulting in multiple payment entries in the order's payment_history). In those cases follow precondition rules for selecting and validating the payment_method_id and obtain explicit user confirmation before charging a different payment method unless the user already provided a clear authorization.",
    "rationale": "Trajectories show the system applying an additional charge to a different payment method (e.g., charging PayPal for a price increase while the original order was paid with a gift card). The blanket ban on split payments at act time contradicted real flows for exchange/modification price differences and needs to be refined to permit charging a different method for price differences with safeguards.",
    "source_task_ids": [
      72
    ]
  },
  {
    "op": "MODIFY",
    "section": "precondition_rules",
    "target_id": "prec-003",
    "content": "IF performing any charge or refund → THEN ensure the specified payment_method_id exists in get_user_details(payment_methods). Default to the original payment method from the order's payment_history for refunds and for any additional charges arising from exchanges/modifications unless the customer explicitly requests a different payment method or the original method lacks sufficient funds. If the original payment method is of type gift_card, check its available balance (from get_user_details/payment method metadata) before attempting to charge it; if the balance is sufficient, use the gift card by default. If the original method lacks sufficient funds, inform the user of the exact shortfall and offer options: (a) provide an alternate payment method, (b) charge the remainder to a different payment method (with the user's explicit confirmation), (c) pause/hold the requested change until the user supplies payment, or (d) cancel the change request. Require explicit user confirmation before charging a payment method different from the original unless the user has already given an unambiguous authorization to proceed with that different method.",
    "rationale": "Trajectories show modifications where additional charges were applied to a different payment method than the original (e.g., gift card + PayPal). The existing rule defaulted only refunds to the original method; it should also define default behavior for charges, gift-card balance checks, shortfall handling, and requirement for explicit confirmation when switching payment methods.",
    "source_task_ids": [
      72
    ]
  }
]

