    "content": "IF a product variant or compatibility/option is needed to propose an exchange or modification OR the user supplies a numeric identifier that might be either a product_id or an item_id → THEN: (a) first try get_product_details(product_id=<provided_id>) when the user-provided id appears to be a product_id; (b) call list_all_product_types to find likely product_ids and call get_product_details(product_id) to inspect variant item_ids, options, availability, and price; (c) if get_product_details(product_id=<provided_id>) returns not found, search the product catalog's variants for a matching item_id (treating the provided id as a variant/item_id) and, if found, use the corresponding product_id and item_id for the proposed exchange/modification; (d) if no match is found, ask the user to clarify whether the number they provided is a product id or an item id before proceeding.",
