    "content": "IF a user requests refunds/returns to be applied to a different payment method than the original order's payment_history → THEN: For standard refunds from returns (i.e., returning delivered items), refund to the original payment method from the order's payment_history by default and refuse requests to route such refunds to payment methods not in the user's account or to another customer's method. EXCEPTION: For exchanges or price-difference adjustments (including delivered-order exchanges and pending-order modifications) the customer may explicitly request that any charge or refund related to the exchange/modification be applied to a different payment method in their account; in those cases verify the requested payment_method_id belongs to the user (per prec-003) and, if the system supports it, honor the request and include payment_method_id in the tool call. If the requested alternate payment method is not in the user's account or is otherwise disallowed, refuse and offer to escalate to a human agent.",
